reviews.review_text: Hot show/ outstanding audience recording Better than a SBD because the audience noise is just at the right level and the bass is deep.  Sugaree voted best ever by Duprees Diamond News.  The rest of the show cooks too.

Great Show, Great Aud Recording Over the years us DeadHeads have learned how to deal with so-so Aud Recordings. Because the music under the layers of disruption, ie: talkers, poor recording equip. and lower gen copies, has usually been well worth the effort to bend the ear a bit to listen through the rough recordings and usually end up being rather satisfying! 
This tape however will not fall under that catagory. THIS AUD RECORDING IS GREAT AND EXCITING!! You won't have to bend an ear or work hard to hear the great music from this show!!
Since the SBDs have been left only as a streaming format for us. I have been exploring these Gems of AUD tapes, every once in a while I will find one that just kicks-ass, this is one of those recordings!! Not only is the recording clear,  spacious, right up front, the Drums are strong and have bounce, But the band is playing very well! I agree that this Sugaree is very powerful, Jerry's guitar is so clear and tight. Also check out Birdsong and Jack Straw. the 2nd set opens with Help>Slip>Franklins nice version, also check out the snappy Eyes, a bit speedy, but still very enjoyable and nice to hear quick licks from Jerry, clocks in at over 9 mins, can you recognize the little jam at the end, maybe Beatles, not sure.....haha... and finally a great China Doll!! Jerry's guitar jumps out of the speakers and seeps into you mind, and like a warm colorful flower, blooms. Vocals are very nice...  
I was at this show, and saw the majority of my 350+ shows through 79-87... many people have opinions about the early eighties... Compared to the the 60's-70's, it's no contest, they dead played so differently in the 60's & 70's and were on that exploratory plane, it's almost apples to oranges to compare the different eras. I love 60's & 70's Dead, however because of my age, I was to young for shows in those days...What they were doing in the eighties was still far better than anything else out there on the Rock and Roll market. And quite Frankly, IMHO an excellent all around musical experience, The Best!! Of Course Jerry had some tough nights, but overall, no complaints from me, I'd do it all over again and even more if I had the chance! Thank you Jerry!!
If you're digging Auds, download this, it's really good!!

Sick AUD/Intense! this has long been my favorite 85 show!

this source is better than the board! the board pitch is waaaaay too fast in the first set, and this is just as clean as it gets, with a SMOKING jack straw>sugaree>rooster....listen to the crowd get wild...

what a sick 1-2-3 opener. INTENSE!!!!....arguably one of the best sugaree's ever!

please get this...You are forewarned though. if you listen to this while driving, you will be compelled to FLOOR IT!!!!!!!
Enjoy this great AUD
Rip is right I agree with ripcurl this is good stuff. I have no issues with '85 and this AUD is very nice. Jerrys vocals could be louder but I think I said that after every show. Nice work guys.

Thank God for this Site I've only seen about 20 live Dead shows (1981-1985), but I've always cherished them (well, a few clunkers, but that's the beauty if it).

I was at this show, and during the third solo of Sugaree my friend and I just looked at one another and we knew what we were thinking...the coolest moment of any show I've seen.

Listen to this one - it will curl your hair, even if you're bald now like me.  The rest of the show is good as well and this is a great AUD recording.

sugaree I too was at this show and the band was pretty rockin. the sugaree as mentioned was outstanding. First set has plenty of energy and the second set is well played and post space is very nice. 3 1/2 tito's for this gig.

One of my Fav's from Spring 85 Simply had a blast at this rather small arena this eve. Standing fdc 15 feet in front of Jer and Bob (slightly to the right of Bob to avoid being spit on ;-) Great energy thru both sets. Super duo of Jack Straw/Sugaree to kick things off. Love the half cocked intro into Est. out of Franklins. I don't normally point out drums/space but this one is a fun one to crank up (might be a good space to blast over the front porch for the kiddies this Halloween). Classic high pace 85 energy. If you like this time period this show is worth the dl. Oade's make great tapes but for this show I like this Nak source better.

Solid 4 on the show.
4.5 for another great aud.

Speed Metal Jackstraw and Sugaree help you realize that Jerry was the fastest guitar player alive, at least who could make each note sound like a note and play that fast.....

Let it Grow is is a tutorial in fiendish.  If it wasn't the Dead, you'd be pretty scared.  They might even have given themselves the willies.
WOW Friends there is nothing more to say. WOW!

Fantastic sounding and outstanding list!!! Another great show from '85 and this one's a real smoker! Used to have a tape of this back in the day, great to hear it again. Outstanding AUD IMHO! I am so glad this website is here with all this great stuff!

Best of 85 This has to be it.  If there's a better one, I'd like to hear it.  The first set is the stuff of dreams.  I certainly never attended one like this, after which the second set is just gravy.  Near best-ever versions of Jack Straw and Sugaree and excellent performances of Bird Song and Let It Grow.  And a very hot second set to follow.  The sound is FAR better than my old tape.  I never did make a copy of the second set, so this will be a nice add.
Best Sugaree ever Great show. 5 minutes from my hometown. It seemed every where you turned there was some one you knew. Last time the Dead played there.
sounds good/can't download! This is an audience apparently but downloading is not happening. why? i got shut out this night--would love to hear it if 25 years later.
Good Show Good show with a worthy AUD for download.  I love the year 1985, lots of good stuff going on here, check it out.

Too bad :( I'm not sure anymore if these stars are for the actual recording or the show but...

This is an excellent recording but their playing does it no justice.  Really, quite a shame.

It's so rare to get exceptional auds that when the music doesn't jibe it just plain ruins it.

So sad.  I wanted to dl this too.

birdsong too Suguree is excellent as noted all around.  Franklins is very good, esp break after "when you get confused..."  Don't see much mention of birdsong in the reviews, but it is very nice.  Early on, around 4 minute mark its got a nice melodius dark star feel to it.

Birdsong Straight from Jerry I had just turned 17 on Phil's birthday...in the front row directly in front of Jerry...and was (as the previous night) completely in "awe" of this incredible band!  Very small venue, and had never seen the band so close to the end of the stage!  They were right on top of us (especially Bobbby). 
As my title reads, during the "swinging" chord intro of Birdsong, Jerry had a big fat grin on his face staring at me(!)...as I was attempting to remain comfortable on the "squished" gen adm floor.  I'm sure Jerry knew and was telling me to R-E-L-A-X. Well I did and had a great time along with the rest of the smallish crowd. 
Agreed Sugaree is awesome (the best though --hmmmmm???)....but the jam in Let it Grow is on fire (probably the best I've heard), and a great 1st set ender. The second set for me takes off during space through Good Lovin'.  Very good '85 intensity!  
Overall a very nice show with some real gems, but the night before was overall more solid IMHO. 
As for this recording?  WOW!!!  I wish the music always sounded so "full"....and still felt like you're in the audience. Better sounding than first night. 
PS --I saw Phil eating KFC out of a bucket behind his rack just before coming on stage!  Must've been running late!!!

Happy 30th 3/25/85 Good time to be a Grateful Dead fan - senior year in high school and the band was playin' all over New England! Those were some great times we will never take for granted and always be appreciative! This special night kicked off a great 1985 with stops in Providence, Saratoga, Hershey not to mention the Fall Tour! Fantastic Aud recording. Much thanks to all the tapers who have participated in preserving these memories. Mike James - where are you?
